tps://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=dock&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL8AC6483E&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Dock</a>, choose a light or dark appearance, change the desktop picture, and more.</p><p>To change System Preferences on your Mac, click the System Preferences icon <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/d76edd35367341480f3747218b92861c.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"34\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_SystemPreference_osx.png\"> in the Dock or choose Apple menu <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/e043ddf1a45711e13f0b30612db65e21.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo.png\"> &gt; System Preferences.</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openApp?bundleId=com.apple.systempreferences\" class=\"URL\">Open System Preferences for me</a></p><div id=\"mchl317dfdd9\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Explore preferences</h2><p>Options for your Mac are organized into preferences. For example, options you can set for Spotlight are located in Spotlight preferences.</p><p>Preferences appear as a grid of icons; the icons shown may vary depending on your Mac and the apps you have installed. Click an icon to open a preference pane and see the options.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/872398e48df73a9a5dc50ae6a6468aa6.png\" alt=\"System Preferences window showing the grid of icons. Click the Show All button in the window’s toolbar to see system preferences as a list, or change how the grid looks.\" height=\"383\" width=\"467\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0007_SystemPref.png\"></figure><p>By default, preferences are arranged in rows by category. To see them in alphabetical order, choose View &gt; Organize Alphabetically.</p></div><div id=\"mchl01d63a5f\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Set options</h2><p>Each preference pane contains options you can set. Most panes include a Help button <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/dd619303b5f54d9dcefa945d734869f4.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"31\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_FinderHelp_osx.png\"> to click for more information about the options.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/9279c05c324f9557b2054cd263b98bbe.png\" alt=\"Click Show All to see all preference icons. Click the Help button to get more information about the pane.\" height=\"339\" width=\"467\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0005_DockPrefs.png\"></figure><p>Some panes are locked to protect your Mac, indicated by a closed lock icon <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/314aad0915d1135d3070820482bc2166.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_LockSysPrefs_osx.png\"> at the bottom of the pane, and the options are dimmed. To unlock a pane so you can set options, click the lock icon, then enter the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=administrator&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL17F139FC&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">administrator</a> password for your Mac.</p></div><div id=\"mchl24022a74\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Find options</h2><p>If you don’t know where to find an option in System Preferences, use the search field at the top of the window. Options that match your search text are listed, and the preference panes where they’re located are highlighted.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/7af891ca98881b8301ea5cb610cfed86.png\" alt=\"System preferences window showing “zoom” in the search field, a list of matching search results below the search field, and three preference icons highlighted.\" height=\"326\" width=\"467\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0009_SysPrefSearch.png\"></figure></div><p>If you see a red badge on the System Preferences icon in the Dock, you need to take one or more actions. For example, if you didn’t fully set up iCloud, the badge appears on the icon in the Dock; when you click the icon, iCloud preferences are displayed so you can complete setup.</p><p>To change options for an app, such as Mail or Safari, open the app, click the app’s name in the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=menu-bar&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL385F1EEA&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">menu bar</a>, then choose Preferences.</p><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-icloud&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36834&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Set up iCloud</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=use-the-built-in-help&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=HLPVW003&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use built-in help on your Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS Mojave 10.14","IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexON","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"